  "text": "The results depicted in Figures 3, 4 , 5, and 6 are consistent with those that were generated from a smaller data set [CITATION_1] . That data set from PNNL consisted of 3373 spectra of unique peptides from Salmonella Typhimurium. The peptides that we selected from the PNNL data set had a mass that ranged from 600 to 3000 Da and an Xcorr score of at least 2.5. We may conclude that together these two sets of results accurately depict the relative improvement in performance of the SNN peak selection method over that of PepNovo+ and pNovo.",
